# Git: Pull Before Working

At the start of every conversation, before reading files or making any changes, run:

```bash
git pull
```

If there are uncommitted local changes, run `git stash` first, then `git pull`, then `git stash pop`.

This prevents duplicate work from parallel conversations or PRs that have already been merged.
